 Vainne: <br>
  You're right about the acquired taste thing, it's mostly musicians that take to them right away.  Funny though,  even though it takes longer for people who aren't musicians to 'get' it, once they do they're hooked, and it opens up a whole new world for them. =)<br>
<br>
I disagree with the 30 year olds in ponytails playing in garages stereotype though.  If you'd ever been to a Dream Theater concert I doubt you'd have the same opinion. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   They have short hair, wear normal clothes, and play some of the most incredibly intense rock music I've ever heard.<br>
